<div class="sg-panel">
  <h2>Overview</h2>

  <p>Cards are devices that link to a piece content or an action. Housed in a neat box-out is a combination of titles, imagery, summary and a direct action links. These come in a number of variations:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Basic cards</li>
    <li>Course cards (plus subtle variant)</li>
    <li>Project cards</li>
  </ul>

  <p>We'll tackle each of those in a second, but first an important note:</p>

  <p>
    <strong>Cards will always take up 100% of the width of their parent element</strong>. To arrange them
    into columns you should use the <%= link_to "grid system", page_path('layout', 'grid-system') %> provided.
    The examples shown here are width-limited to a three column layout, but that isn't the default layout for a series of cards.
  </p>

  <p>Be sure to familiarise yourself with the grid if you haven't already.</p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Basic Cards</h2>

  <p>The most basic card. Intended for cases such as search results that include a title and call-to-action link.</p>

  <p>These cards are largely style-agnostic, relying on standard typographical elements and component styles in order to build up the contents of each. At their most basic level, an info card allows you to define if heading, body and footer.</p>

  <div class="sg-example">
    <h3 class="sg-example__heading">Example</h3>

    <div class="sg-example__preview">
      <div class="sg-example__card">

        <div class="o-card">
          <div class="o-card__heading">Beware of:</div>

          <div class="o-card__body">
            <ul class="c-list c-list--bulleted">
              <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">The dog</li>
              <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">The lion</li>
              <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">The hulk</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="o-card__footer"><a class="o-card__footer-link" href="#">Find out more</a></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <code class="sg-example__code">
      &lt;div class="o-card"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class="o-card__heading"&gt;Beware of:&lt;/div&gt;<br>
      <br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class="o-card__body"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ul class="c-list c-list--bulleted"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted"&gt;The dog&lt;/li&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted"&gt;The lion&lt;/li&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted"&gt;The hulk&lt;/li&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/ul&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class="o-card__footer"&gt;&lt;a class="o-card__footer-link" href="#"&gt;Find out more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
      &lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </div>

  <h3>Cards with Secondary Call-To-Action</h3>

  <p>In some cases you may require cards that each have a primary and secondary call to action. A button in the body and plain link in the card's footer is a good way to achieve this.</p>

  <div class="sg-example">
    <h3 class="sg-example__heading">Example</h3>

    <div class="sg-example__preview">
      <div class="sg-example__card">

        <div class="o-card">
          <div class="o-card__body">
            <h4>Lauren Holt</h4>
            <p class="c-meta">0.4 miles away</p>
            <a href="" class="c-button c-button--block c-button--hollow c-button--green">Contact Volunteer</a>
          </div>
          <div class="o-card__footer">
            <a class="o-card__footer-link" href="#">Add volunteer to club</a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <code class="sg-example__code">
      &lt;div class="o-card"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class="o-card__body"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h4&gt;St Mary's Catholic Primary School&lt;/h4&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p class="c-meta">0.4 miles away&lt;/p&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p class="u-text--center"&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Contact Club Host&lt;/a>&lt;/p&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
      &lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </div>

  <h3>Even More Basic Cards</h3>

  <p>On occasion you'll find that your cards don't need a heading or footer. Just omit them and use basic typographical styles to build the content of the card:</p>

  <div class="sg-example">
    <h3 class="sg-example__heading">Example</h3>

    <div class="sg-example__preview">
      <div class="sg-example__card">

        <div class="o-card">
          <div class="o-card__body">
            <h4>St Mary's Catholic Primary School</h4>
            <p class="c-meta">0.4 miles away</p>
            <p class="u-text--center"><a href="#">Contact Club Host</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <code class="sg-example__code">
      &lt;div class="o-card"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div class="o-card__body"&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h4&gt;St Mary's Catholic Primary School&lt;/h4&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p class="c-meta">0.4 miles away&lt;/p&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p class="u-text--center"&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Contact Club Host&lt;/a>&lt;/p&gt;<br>
      &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
      &lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </div>

</div>

